_ There flows the stream Sgimrashuli In Sasashi village... I was a child then...
_ mere sopel sasai, me main bavvi viqavi, ik sgimrauli {a}modis, ele.
lamara oniani-liarelianisa (svanuri enis laxuri dialekis carmomadgeneli) carmartuli desascauli kvemo svaneti da erasias ambavi.
Speaker: Lamara Oniani (LS). A pagan feast in Lower Svanetia and the story of Eprasia. Video 29; (00:44:15:640_00:48:48:640).
ale sgimraul amxen mindor xr i desascaul li exu lunu sasisa.
There is a field on this side of Sgimrashuli and there was a Svan feast in Sasashi.
am sgimraulis aket mindoria ("akvs") da sasai aris erti svanuri desascauli.
mi maqid ale, miga libpi bild.
I remember it sweetly; it was in my childhood.
me maxsovs es, em{s} bavvobai bilad.
They used to make dinner for praising God.
They had a beautiful "pikali". "Pikali" is a bakery made of stone.
al as alaonarl 'asqdax, ukn lemes xda,
This pikali was made like a tower-bell, fire was set at the bottom.
am pikals "alaonivit" ("pikali kvisagan gaetebuli uris sacxobi") gaaetebdnen xolme, kvemodan cecxli ento,
gbar... mdas... aesdax agixen, lcomae coms,
In big bowls... that... they would carry from home some kneaded dough,
gobebit... is ("imas")... mihkondat ("caiebdnen") inidan, mozelili comi ("mocomil coms"),
i titeuli oax u xunda mine-mine ale lanq eria.
and each family had this bakery hearth of its own.
da tvitoeul oaxs tav-tavisi es gamosacxobi eria hkonda.
They used to bake "tablas" here; ( "tabla" - sacrificial bread shaped like board).
oaxars amzrdax i rdax eu mindorisa.
They would bless the families and stay there in the field.
oaxebs dalocavdnen xolme da iqvnen ik mindori.

Once, when they were praying in this field applying to God,
ertxel, roca am mindori loculobdnen turme ("naloceban") da merts evedrebodnen ("naxveceban"),

A twelve-year-old girl has gone there with her people
tormei clis gogo casula tavis xalxtan ertad ik
ladbs, ser lidbs xaldad, limxrci i lidb.
while praying, in short, we call it "Libdashi" so, here are "Limkharci" and "Lidbashi"
limxrci eann daemtxa al... anlebuno, anlebuno yed ladeuno li al limxrci.
Afterwards "Limkharci" coincided with Ascension Day... "Limkharci" is ten days after Ascension Day...
"limxarci" mere daemtxva amalebas ("amalebis emdeg"), amalebis emdeg ati dis emdeg aris "limxarci".

am gogonas aeina turme ik, sanam urs gamoacxobdnen misi oaxis cevrebi

and when she woke up, she looked... there... there was a hole...
da rom aeina turme, rom gauviia, euxedavs, ik... imas kmnili... qopila, gaxvreili,
i sg'r alsgidnli extysa, imayena ka xcda eyi, ere od amx te xomina,
and when she looked through it, she saw something... something like!...
da rom euxedavs imai, raac daunaxavs iseti, rom sanam morialebula ("aket uknia"),
ue nin sg'tqeda i deymo ka lmgrglin i ims atgnena i gagiebulan.
it seemed that she had lost her tongue and she could not speak and she got deaf.... People drove mad...
uve ena avardnia da verc laaraobda turme da daqruebula ("qurs dadgomia") da gagiebulan.
ali amay xoa dina almunli i imsi atgnena.
Such a nice girl got deaf and mute.
es aseti argi gogo damunebula da daqruebula ("qursac dadgomia").
Then they would have her like this.
ales de laxdax i am dros lexumxen emqedlix gelonar, xatxlnax momagrs, momagrs,
They could not help her and that time the Gelovanis arrived from Lechkhuumi, they were looking for a maidservant to hire, a maidservant,
amistvis ("amas") ver uveliat da am dros lexumidan mosulan gelovanebi, moamagires eebdnen turme, moamagires,
and "Well, we will take her," - they said.
otyax ale dina ami, gelon nesors.
cauqvaniat es gogo ak, nesor gelovans.
They, the famous Gelovanis, lived in Spatagori.
isini, cnobili gelovanebi, satagori cxovrobdnen turme ("nasaxleban").
She served them, they had her.
eno sga laxanna ei taad gelon leans, ale.
Then she became pregnant by duke Levan Gelovani, that it is.
mere daorsulebula ("enaorsuleba") is tavad levan gelovanisgan ("gelovan levans"), es.
sg'r laxanna, k'axtenna qin gezal, zurabay osxax,
She became pregnant and gave birth to a baby and they called him Zurab,
rom daorsulebula ("enaorsuleba"), gaunda turme ("gasenia") vaivili ("qini vili"), zurabi daurkmeviat,
mara dsma xanena ea lisdis, eay xoa qin.
and there was no one better to look at, such nice a boy he was.
magram araperi ar ("ara ra") sobda turme imis qurebas, iseti argi bii (qopila).
He was grown up by this deaf and mute woman.
eno gelonar, ue dro er eicala, ale mg aad.
Then the Gelovanis went away, when the time changed, but she did not go.
mere gelovanebi, uve dro rom eicvala, es qvelaperi ("qvela") cavida.
omunisar er sg'nqadx, emedlix yerxi sacxoreblad tbiliste, ierxi _imte, yerxi _imte, ka loxcrax ale.
When communists came, some of them moved to Tbilisi to live there, the others - to some other places
omunisebi rom emovidnen, main zogi tbilisi casula sacxovreblad, zogi _ sad, zogi _ sad, miuovebiat es.
ale ka loxcrax, al zurl, i min mag emedlix ei-a i ale emsed ddaaril.
She was left alone, this woman... they all were dispersed and she was left alone.
es miuovebiat, es kali, da tviton qvelani casulan ikit-aket da es darenila maro.
Zurabi became ill in the army.
When he came back, he had got ill with tuberculosis.
emqedli i mia buba epxanite otyax saste ale samurnalod.
He arrived and his uncle took him to Chepkhan in Sasashi to treat him.
amosula da biamis ("misi biia") epxantan miuqvaniat ("cauiat") sasai es samurnalod.
xoa sgim i xoa haer i xoa mag der irdl ee i samurnalod ee xaqnax,
Good sour water, good air, and surely, everything would be good there, and they took him there to treat him.
argi mave cqali da argi haeri da xom qvelaperi argi ikneboda ik da samurnalod ik hqoliat,
However, he, Zurab, still passed away.
emsed dd eno ale, qru-mun zurl, i emqedli i otyax,
She was left alone, this deaf and mute woman, and they came and took her along with them.
darenila mere es marodmaro, qru-muni kali, da mosula da cauqvaniat ("cauiat"),
emedx alyri, umil, mia telra, alyr mag, otyax sacxorebeld ex, satagorte.
They moved as well _ her brother, sister-in-law, all of them, and they took her to live there, in Spatagori.
casulan esenic, ma, misi rali, eseni qvela, cauqvaniat ("cauiat") sacxovreblad ik, satagori.
ee ser alyrs bpar lehodndax, xomd u lmardlix.
Then they had children there; in short, they were well.
ik uve amat bavvebi eeinat ("miecat"), molet argad qopilan ("namqopan").
aly ame otdxax mia gezalcaxan i alyri rdax gelonare nadgom-namqopi, al oax,
She, too, was buried here, with her child and they also lived on the Gelovanis former place... this family,
esec ak dausaplavebiat ("daumarxavt") tavis viltan ertad da esenic cxovrobdnen ("imqopebodnen") gelovanebis namosaxlarze ("nadgom-namqopze"), es oaxi,
i ale amn limxrci lade ami edblunda ale erasya i xoa dina.
and so she became deaf on the Limkhartsi Feast Day, this Eprasia, a nice girl.
da es ase "limxarcis" desascaulis des ase damunda (dr. "blu") es erasia da argi gogo.
ee ser xy xoa sakme isql, sopel sasisa,
In short, many good things were done there, in the village of Sasashi.
ik molet ("uve, mei") bevri argi sakme etdeboda, sopel sasai,
einar, ere keqni xoa lti, scalul, mayma, tx ropesor ari sasisa,
There are four professors from there among the most distinguished scientists of our country.
imiom ("imistvis"), rom kveqnis gamoreuli ("argi reuli"), scavluli, rac ia, otxi ropesori aris sasai,
aademios ari, mag umales ganatlebul, mara sopelisa dr asad i eannen m li eyi,
There is an academician, they all have higher education, but nobody has been left in the village, and then it was not like that...
aademiosi aris, qvela umalesi ganatlebit, magram sopeli aravin ar dara da mere ar aris ise,
mara mdebareoba sas ali dsa itxi.
But you can find nowhere the site as good as that of Sasashi.
magram mdebareoba sasaisnairi ("qalibi") arsad ar aris ("ioveba").
It is a very nice village.
